293
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:47,580
thinking I'm deaf.

294
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:50,340
When people die, they go to paradise.

295
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,220
Do you understand?

296
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:53,960
When someone's gone,

297
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:54,760
they're gone.

298
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:58,600
How did you get through your childhood?

299
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:01,120
When your mother passed away,

300
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:02,160
you've been through this before.

301
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,890
You trained hard for ten years,

302
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:07,180
and one relationship has ruined you.

303
00:27:08,520 --> 00:27:09,280
You're letting yourself down,

304
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:10,680
and you owe me better too.

305
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:12,520
When you wanted to dance the White Snake,

306
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:13,650
what did you tell me?

307
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:14,880
What did I tell you?

308
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:16,840
Dance has four levels:

309
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:17,930
Good technique,

310
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:19,300
to become a dancer;

311
00:27:20,120 --> 00:27:21,920
Rich inner life and excellence,

312
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:24,200
experiencing love's sweetness and bitterness;

313
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:25,240
Moving yourself

314
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:26,800
and touching others;

315
00:27:27,360 --> 00:27:28,360
The fourth level,

316
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:30,640
experiencing life's partings,

317
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:32,400
understanding gain and loss,

318
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:34,480
to truly become an artist.

319
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:36,440
Are you stupid?

320
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:41,160
Do you need someone else to teach you these things?

321
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:42,820
Don't you understand?

322
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,260
I can't understand it.

323
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:53,520
Look at me.

324
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:58,280
Zhou Tong is gone.

325
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,000
You're alive.

326
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:04,440
Uncle Qiao loves you.

327
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:05,440
Xiaomi loves you.

328
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:07,160
I love you.

329
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:09,440
Everyone who loves you is still alive,

330
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:11,300
but you don't even love yourself.

331
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:17,640
I really don't know what I'm doing here.

332
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:22,280
Who am I?

333
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:24,600
Director.

334
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:29,320
I flew all the way here,

335
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:32,260
is the director here to make your bed?

336
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:34,840
No.

337
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:38,500
Straight talk,

338
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:41,360
are you dancing in 'White Snake' or not?

339
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:47,100
Look at what kind of place this is.

340
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:52,120
You might as well stay here forever,

341
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:54,440
teaching kids in dance classes,

342
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:56,810
I wouldn't even recognize a youth center.

343
00:28:58,680 --> 00:28:59,740
Let's just do that.

344
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:03,860
I'll retire early too,

345
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:05,620
go back to Beijing.

346
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:08,680
I'll teach kids to flail around too.

347
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:10,200
Then I'll go to the

348
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:11,200
square,

349
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:13,460
teach dancing to middle-aged women.

350
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,080
Life is just

351
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:16,360
getting by, isn't it?

352
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,410
The two of us,

353
00:29:20,080 --> 00:29:22,000
north and south, 30 years apart,

354
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:24,320
both retiring early.

355
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:26,490
Who hasn't been in love?

356
00:29:28,280 --> 00:29:29,360
When I was in love,

357
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:30,640
I was desperate too.

358
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:37,880
If I had known it would be like this,

359
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:39,610
I should have given up long ago.

360
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:42,160
Can't train spineless people like you.

361
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,560
I'm here, Xiaoyao.

362
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:18,120
Xiaoyao.

363
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:12,400
Hello.

364
00:31:12,520 --> 00:31:13,480
Do you have any rooms available?

365
00:31:13,480 --> 00:31:14,520
May I see your ID card, please?

366
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:14,880
Sure.

367
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:16,320
Hello.

368
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:19,600
Hello.

369
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:22,200
I'm staying in room 312.

370
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,800
Can he stay with me tonight?

371
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,000
Are you relatives?

372
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:29,800
Yes.

373
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:33,060
Will you be staying tomorrow as well?

374
00:31:33,120 --> 00:31:33,780
No, I won't.

375
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,460
I won't be staying either.

376
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:37,000
Then you can check out

377
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:38,960
and he can register for a one-day stay.

378
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:39,960
No refund needed.

379
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:40,600
That's fine.

380
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:43,160
Could both of you give me your ID cards, please?

381
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:43,490
Okay.

382
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:44,850
Here.

383
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:45,840
Thank you.

384
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:48,780
Thanks.

385
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:52,170
I came all the way from Beijing to find you.

386
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,040
Whether you go back or not

387
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:54,700
is up to you.

388
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:55,800
Go back,

389
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:57,730
rise from the ashes.

390
00:31:58,400 --> 00:31:59,200
Don't go back,

391
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,250
and you're just a loser.

392
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:06,170
Alright,

393
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:08,160
do I need to get a new access card?

394
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:12,200
Thank you.

395
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:38,250
Wen Xiaoyao.

396
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:45,120
Am I still your director?

397
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:49,480
You will always be, for life.

398
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:51,410
I don't want to talk about forever,

399
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:52,920
are you now or not?

400
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,200
Yes.

401
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:57,320
Come back,

402
00:32:58,880 --> 00:33:00,600
we'll restage 'The Legend of the White Snake.'

403
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:01,760
Even if I compromise completely

404
00:33:01,760 --> 00:33:02,520
and we perform

405
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:04,650
Yang Yunxin's 'The Stringed Zither,'

406
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:06,080
you still must come back.

407
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:10,890
You are a professional dancer,

408
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:13,180
not a professional romantic.

409
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:16,200
Perform 'The Stringed Zither.'

410
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:20,480
The ballet company is going through a transition,

411
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,240
I've stepped back to a supporting role.

412
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:23,680
Yang Yunxin has choreographed a dance

413
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:25,410
called 'The Stringed Zither.'

414
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:26,680
Bai Suzhen and Xiaoqing,

415
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:27,540
you and Qiaomi.

416
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:29,460
What about Xu Xian?

417
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:36,160
Immortals live for thousands of years,

418
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:38,130
mortals are just passing through.

419
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,200
There's one more dish

420
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:48,460
take your time eating.

421
00:33:49,120 --> 00:33:50,180
One dish is enough,

422
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:51,700
have you eaten?

423
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:54,130
I can't eat anything at all.

424
00:34:09,639 --> 00:34:10,480
Want some soup?

425
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:11,139
Never mind,

426
00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:12,360
it's too much trouble.

427
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:13,290
It's no trouble.

428
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,199
What was that thing

429
00:34:16,360 --> 00:34:17,820
you really wanted in life?

430
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:20,800
A food processor.

431
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:22,449
It's not on sale yet.

432
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,199
Why did you rush back?

433
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:28,090
I was afraid you'd be with Wen Xiaoyao.

434
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:29,840
Why would you think that?

435
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:34,100
I couldn't help it.

436
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:37,600
Zhou Tong is dead.

437
00:34:40,679 --> 00:34:41,360
I know.

438
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:48,480
You know?

439
00:34:50,239 --> 00:34:51,639
I told her not to tell you,

440
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,530
why did she tell you anyway?

441
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:09,440
The wiring should have been replaced during renovation.

442
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,200
It's all old.

443
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:28,340
The day Zhou Tong came,

444
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:31,260
the power went out too.

445
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:06,240
I went to check the circuit breaker.

446
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:08,250
I'll just say a few words and leave.

447
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:19,440
Before my flight to Guangzhou took off,

448
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:21,930
Wen Xiaoyao told me Zhou Tong was dead.

449
00:36:23,560 --> 00:36:25,360
I wanted to come back right away.

450
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:28,440
Why?

451
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:30,970
With Zhou Tong gone,

452
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:34,320
Wen Xiaoyao would be with you.

453
00:36:39,680 --> 00:36:41,280
Do you have to think that way?

454
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:43,850
While I was checking in, I thought,

455
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,760
maybe I shouldn't go through with it,

456
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:49,120
since Wen Xiaoyao had already come to Hangzhou.

457
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:51,180
Wen Xiaoyao has nothing to do with me.

458
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:55,700
Zhou Tong is the one who matters to me.

459
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:59,130
What's your relationship with Zhou Tong?

460
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:03,100
Don't you understand?

461
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:04,040
I do.

462
00:37:05,720 --> 00:37:06,680
He's the chain.

463
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:08,640
In the end,

464
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:11,680
connecting you and Wen Xiaoyao.

465
00:37:17,120 --> 00:37:17,920
You're crazy.

466
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:19,920
I love you.

467
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:23,160
Me too.

468
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:27,040
Don't be angry.

469
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:29,480
I'm not.

470
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:31,960
At our engagement party,

471
00:37:33,440 --> 00:37:34,970
Mom summed things up for us.

472
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:38,610
What did she say?

473
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:42,280
You're with me

474
00:37:43,080 --> 00:37:44,480
because you feel secure,

475
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,760
not because of love.

476
00:37:47,560 --> 00:37:48,420
I'm good to you,

477
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:51,300
so you promise to be good to me too.

478
00:37:52,320 --> 00:37:53,580
Actually, the two of us

479
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:54,960
never properly dated.

480
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:57,360
Why do you remember all this?

481
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,700
I can't help it.

482
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:04,890
Some things stick in my memory.

483
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:06,530
Some things.

484
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:08,810
Were you like this with him before?

485
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:14,840
I don't want to talk about the past.

486
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:17,100
Or is it that you can't remember the past?

487
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,000
Where's the ring?

488
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:24,050
Let me see it.

489
00:38:51,160 --> 00:38:51,960
Try it on.

490
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:03,850
Perfect fit.

491
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:07,490
Perfect.

492
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:10,010
Will you always wear it?

493
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:12,080
Yes.

494
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:17,440
Even if you're not with me?

495
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:19,730
We'll definitely be together.

496
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:22,860
You keep your word.

497
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:24,960
Yes.

498
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:29,770
But I'm not good.

499
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:32,420
I can't help it,

500
00:39:33,920 --> 00:39:35,180
it's always like this.

501
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:37,640
It's okay.

502
00:39:41,760 --> 00:39:43,220
Why is there another pair?

503
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:44,260
They came free.

504
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:48,740
Since she's come to Hangzhou,

505
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:50,850
you two should be together,

506
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:53,130
and forget about me.

507
00:39:54,840 --> 00:39:57,240
I never really did anything for you anyway.

508
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:59,620
You ran away the first time we met.

509
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:02,360
I hope I won't forget you,

510
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:05,520
but if things continue like this,

511
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:07,850
someday I won't be able to control myself.

512
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:09,480
By then,

513
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:12,640
I won't leave you with any good impression,

514
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:16,050
so I might as well be nice to you now.

515
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:01,400
I'm heading back.

516
00:41:02,680 --> 00:41:04,560
Tomorrow we'll look for Wen Xiaoyao together.

517
00:41:04,560 --> 00:41:05,440
What for?

518
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:07,610
Then who do you want to find?

519
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:09,200
Zhou Tong.

520
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:11,280
It's all the same anyway.

521
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:29,180
South Asian Driver

522
00:43:33,080 --> 00:43:34,210
On-set Art Director

523
00:43:50,040 --> 00:43:51,300
DI Process Supervisor

524
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:07,080
Music Arrangement
